Honest review⤵️

If you’re looking to splurge on your hair care, the @Olaplex No. 4 Shampoo and No. 5 Conditioner are definitely worth considering! 

The shampoo lathers beautifully with just a dime-sized amount. It cleanses my scalp deeply without stripping it, which I love. It even removes hair oil in just one wash which is rare for me! 

The conditioner makes my hair super soft, smooth, and less frizzy, plus it adds a nice shine. 

Overall, the duo is definitely worth the hype but I would not repurchase the conditioner again as there are many alternatives in the market that give me the same result at a much lower price. 

Overall rating for the duo: 8/10

Let’s talk: Dark Circles! 

You can’t get rid of dark circles. Yes, you read that correctly! Most people have genetic dark circles which cannot be permanently treated solely with skincare. However , there are a few things you can do to reduce them and prevent further damage. 

Lifestyle changes: 
😴sleep at least 8 hours
📱reduce screen time
☀️use SPF under your eyes
🥬eat a balanced diet

Treatments:
🧴use a retinol based eye cream daily
🧊cold compress using cucumber to reduce swelling and improve dark circles
👩‍🔬try a laser treatment or fillers if your issue is severe

Share your tips/ favourite products to reduce dark circles in the comments below.
